Governor Simon Lalong of Plateau State has sacked all cabinet 24hours to his inauguration for the second term as the Governor of the State. Amongst those sacked by Lalong to include the State Executive Council Members, Special Advisers, Legislative Liaisons, and Senior Special Assistants, Special Assistants as well as Local Government Liaison officers and such other Political appointees. Lalong in a Press Statement signed and issue by the Acting Secretary to the State Government Mr Richard Tokma said the dissolution also affects chairmen and members of commissions, boards and Parastatals except statutory commissions specified in the Constitution. The Statement said that the Attorney General and Commissioner for Justice is to remain in office pending the reconstitution of the State Executive Council. Lalong, however, appreciated the appointees for their contributions and wish them success in their future endeavours.